* [[Carolinas Aviation Museum]], [[Charlotte, North Carolina|Charlotte]], [[North Carolina]], USA has Medal of Honor Mike Clausen's CH-46
* [[Flying Leatherneck Aviation Museum]], [[San Diego]], [[California]], USA has &quot;Lady Ace 09&quot; of [[HMM-165]]. The CH-46 took part in [[Operation Frequent Wind]] and was used to evacuate Ambassador [[Graham Martin]], the last [[United States Ambassador to South Vietnam]] from the [[United States Embassy, Saigon]] on 30 April 1975.
* [[National Museum of Naval Aviation]]
* [[National Museum of the Marine Corps]]
* [[USS Midway Museum]] in San Diego, California

